# Notifications and email — where to look

## For humans and agents (maintenance)

- **Written matrix (product “what / when / transport”):** [`.cursor/plans/notifications-email-inapp-catalog.plan.md`](mdc:.cursor/plans/notifications-email-inapp-catalog.plan.md) — update this when behavior, subjects, or threading rules change.
- **Implementation runbook:** [`.cursor/plans/notifications-catalog-alignment.plan.md`](mdc:.cursor/plans/notifications-catalog-alignment.plan.md).
- **What the repo actually implements:** [`src/lib/notifications/notification-catalog.ts`](mdc:src/lib/notifications/notification-catalog.ts) (`CATALOG_ID`, prefs notes, `portfolioFollowedThreadId`, `inferInboxFilterCategory`, `showInternalNotificationInboxFilter`, inbox helpers).
- **All send paths:** search for `sendTransactionalEmail` and `sendEmailByGmail` under `src/`.
- **Rendered email samples:** JSDoc + behavior on [`src/app/api/platform/notifications/smoketest/route.ts`](mdc:src/app/api/platform/notifications/smoketest/route.ts).

Prefer **updating the plan + `notification-catalog.ts` in the same change** when you add a new notification kind or transport so the inventory stays truthful.

## Thread ids (in-app `notifications.data`)

- Weekly recap: `weekly:{userId}:{runWeekEnding}`, role `head`.
- Onboarding: `onboarding:{userId}`; welcome milestones use role `child` where applicable.
- Followed portfolio (rebalance, entries/exits, price move): `portfolio:{userId}:{profileId}`, role `child` — use `portfolioFollowedThreadId` from `notification-catalog.ts`; writers in [`cron-fanout.ts`](mdc:src/lib/notifications/cron-fanout.ts).

DB overview: [`.cursor/rules/supabase-schema.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/supabase-schema.mdc) (Notifications bullet).

## Inbox filter chips (bell)

Mapping lives in `inferInboxFilterCategory` (same file). **`internal`** = rows with `catalog_id` `internal.smoketest_seed` (operator seed). The **Internal (dev)** chip renders when `NODE_ENV === 'development'` or `NEXT_PUBLIC_SHOW_INTERNAL_NOTIFICATION_FILTER=1`; otherwise those rows only appear under **All**.

## Why not duplicate everything in `docs/` or always-on rules?

- Long tables belong in **`.cursor/plans/`** (this repo’s versioned plan location; see [repo-plans-location](mdc:.cursor/rules/repo-plans-location.mdc)).
- A **short, agent-requestable rule** (this file) gives Cursor a stable hook without pasting large tables into every chat.
